1
00:00:58,408 --> 00:01:02,643
[In-season Angry Snapper]
- Yes! It's an angry snapper! - Angry!

2
00:01:10,992 --> 00:01:12,710
What?

3
00:01:13,992 --> 00:01:18,783
Man, another bust today.

4
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:23,442
<i>Meet another cell who's half-unemployed now.</i>

5
00:01:23,442 --> 00:01:25,451
<i>Fishing Cell.</i>

6
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:39,090
<i>894 days of going home with nothing.</i>

7
00:01:47,492 --> 00:01:48,717
<i>And then...</i>

8
00:01:48,717 --> 00:01:51,542
<i>Then came day 895.</i>

9
00:01:58,783 --> 00:02:01,730
- Angry!
- I caught one!

10
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:04,615
<i>At last, he hooked one.</i>

11
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,700
- An angry snapper!
- Angry!

12
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,075
- It's the angry snapper!
<i>- Angry snapper.</i>

13
00:02:09,075 --> 00:02:12,783
<i>It's a rare fish only caught
when Yumi gets mad.</i>

14
00:02:12,783 --> 00:02:16,461
<i>The angry snapper
came back from near extinction...</i>

15
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:23,950
It's an angry snapper!

16
00:02:23,950 --> 00:02:25,950
<i>right when PD Shin forgot all his manners.</i>

17
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:26,992
Angry!

18
00:02:26,992 --> 00:02:30,425
<i>I came for those too.</i>

19
00:02:30,425 --> 00:02:32,302
<i>That was the last batch.</i>

20
00:02:32,302 --> 00:02:34,450
<i>They sell out fast.</i>

21
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:36,867
<i>Right. So...</i>

22
00:02:36,867 --> 00:02:38,200
<i>Anyway, I'll get going.</i>

23
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,292
<i>See you next week.</i>

24
00:02:43,996 --> 00:02:46,075
- Score, another angry snapper!
- Angry!

25
00:02:46,075 --> 00:02:49,443
<i>When PD Shin grabbed them all for himself.</i>

26
00:02:49,443 --> 00:02:52,371
<i>But Maltese aren't that smart.</i>

27
00:02:53,197 --> 00:02:54,532
Angry!

28
00:02:54,532 --> 00:02:56,576
<i>Don't all dogs do that?</i>

29
00:02:56,576 --> 00:02:58,875
<i>Unless it's a lizard.</i>

30
00:03:01,205 --> 00:03:04,333
Angry!

31
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:07,500
<i>Maltese... Don't they eat poop?</i>

32
00:03:10,408 --> 00:03:11,817
[PD Shin]

33
00:03:15,908 --> 00:03:19,417
Angry!

34
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,355
- Angry!
- Angry!

35
00:03:26,355 --> 00:03:28,232
It's a full catch!

36
00:03:28,232 --> 00:03:33,120
Yumi's absolutely furious!

37
00:03:37,074 --> 00:03:39,742
Hey, Lullaby Cell, get up.

38
00:03:39,742 --> 00:03:41,158
What is it?

39
00:03:41,158 --> 00:03:43,247
Help Yumi fall asleep.

40
00:03:43,247 --> 00:03:46,042
It's after two in the morning
and she won't sleep.

41
00:03:46,042 --> 00:03:47,917
What?

42
00:03:58,825 --> 00:04:03,450
Seriously, the more I think about it,
the crazier it gets.

43
00:04:05,353 --> 00:04:09,700
<i>♪ Go to sleep, go to sleep, sweet Yumi ♪</i>

44
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:12,068
<i>Since Yumi's too furious to sleep,</i>

45
00:04:12,068 --> 00:04:13,742
<i>- I'm stuck on the clock too.</i>
- Sleep well.

46
00:04:13,742 --> 00:04:16,030
My stomach's empty.

47
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:19,283
Hey, look at the clock. You're hungry again?

48
00:04:19,283 --> 00:04:21,992
I want fried dumplings.

49
00:04:21,992 --> 00:04:24,992
Fried dumplings!

50
00:04:24,992 --> 00:04:28,750
<i>Hungry Cell wants a midnight snack for once.</i>

51
00:04:34,325 --> 00:04:39,625
I'm so ticked off I can't sleep.
That Shin Soon Rok.

52
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:45,893
Hey, Coco.

53
00:04:45,893 --> 00:04:47,561
You can't sleep either?

54
00:04:47,561 --> 00:04:49,689
You're all worked up too, aren't you?

55
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:52,408
It was just humiliating.

56
00:04:52,408 --> 00:04:53,901
I'm so sorry, Coco.

57
00:04:53,901 --> 00:04:55,575
Poor thing.

58
00:04:55,575 --> 00:04:58,197
Sorry I let him say that to you.

59
00:04:58,197 --> 00:05:01,450
That was humiliating, wasn't it?

60
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:03,869
I bet that guy's actually a sociopath.

61
00:05:03,869 --> 00:05:07,506
Who's that heartless to an animal?

62
00:05:08,117 --> 00:05:11,210
Sociopath? Or personality disorder?

63
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:14,046
Or maybe both?

64
00:05:14,046 --> 00:05:16,000
Definitely both.

65
00:05:19,658 --> 00:05:23,700
So how do sociopaths
and personality disorders connect?

66
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:27,283
I bet there are tons of personality disorders.

67
00:05:27,283 --> 00:05:29,667
Let me dig into this.

68
00:05:39,325 --> 00:05:40,950
Oh hey, Bulletin Board Cell.

69
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,908
You're still awake?

70
00:05:42,908 --> 00:05:44,992
I got slammed with new notes.

71
00:05:44,992 --> 00:05:46,575
Can't remember the last time.

72
00:05:46,575 --> 00:05:47,950
[Talking trash about a Maltese?!]

73
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,450
[Replace him, Shin Soon Rok]
[How should we get revenge?]

74
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,272
<i>"Replace him, Shin Soon Rok."</i>

75
00:05:51,272 --> 00:05:54,200
<i>"What a jerk. How do I get back at him?"</i>

76
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:58,041
<i>"He insulted a Maltese?
I'll never forgive him."</i>

77
00:06:02,867 --> 00:06:05,908
Oh no, what now?

78
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:07,533
You need to look after her.

79
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:09,075
Coco's stressed out because of this.

80
00:06:09,075 --> 00:06:11,700
Look, her coat's gone all dull!

81
00:06:13,992 --> 00:06:15,200
Don't let it get you down.

82
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,000
You okay?

83
00:06:20,783 --> 00:06:23,366
Wait, there's no bungeoppang left.

84
00:06:23,366 --> 00:06:28,117
Is he kidding? He took all eight for himself?

85
00:06:28,117 --> 00:06:31,833
You're kidding, there's none left?

86
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:35,117
After the fried dumplings,
it was bungeoppang's turn.

87
00:06:35,117 --> 00:06:37,325
I have to have it, right now!

88
00:06:37,325 --> 00:06:42,583
I'm craving
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang!

89
00:06:44,427 --> 00:06:46,888
Bungeoppang!

90
00:06:46,888 --> 00:06:49,492
Bungeoppang!

91
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:50,783
Hey, you guys!

92
00:06:50,783 --> 00:06:52,825
What's with all this racket
in the middle of the night?

93
00:06:52,825 --> 00:06:56,867
- I have to sleep now to write tomorrow.
- My bungeoppang!

94
00:06:56,867 --> 00:07:00,667
<i>It'd been a while
since the town stayed up all night.</i>

95
00:07:35,492 --> 00:07:37,375
Ready to go?

96
00:07:45,617 --> 00:07:47,490
Man, I'm so tired.

97
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:50,667
Lost so much sleep because of that jerk.

98
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,408
Coco.

99
00:07:53,408 --> 00:07:55,122
Your mom's coming today.

100
00:07:55,122 --> 00:07:57,208
She said she's coming to pick you up.

101
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,542
Lucky you, Coco.

102
00:08:18,325 --> 00:08:20,106
- Isn't that PD Shin?
- What?

103
00:08:20,106 --> 00:08:22,450
Seriously, why do I keep seeing him?

104
00:08:22,450 --> 00:08:26,333
The bungeoppang place is that way.

105
00:08:27,135 --> 00:08:30,533
Don't tell me he's buying bungeoppang already?

106
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:32,917
Like I'm letting that happen.

107
00:08:34,658 --> 00:08:38,033
Hold on, Yumi's wearing those raggedy sweats!

108
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:40,519
And Yumi didn't even wash up!

109
00:08:48,217 --> 00:08:51,708
Like that even matters right now?

110
00:09:13,158 --> 00:09:14,450
Excuse me, sir!

111
00:09:14,450 --> 00:09:15,452
Hello.

112
00:09:15,452 --> 00:09:16,575
- Hello.
- Hi.

113
00:09:16,575 --> 00:09:19,331
Give me every Strawberry Cream
Custard Bungeoppang here.

114
00:09:19,331 --> 00:09:21,374
- Every single one?
- Yes, please.

115
00:09:21,374 --> 00:09:22,542
Every last one.

116
00:09:22,542 --> 00:09:24,322
Oh, is it a group order?

117
00:09:24,322 --> 00:09:26,075
How many per box, then?

118
00:09:26,075 --> 00:09:28,757
Skip the boxes. I'll take whatever's here.

119
00:09:28,757 --> 00:09:32,344
One second, let me count them up.

120
00:09:32,344 --> 00:09:34,137
No, just give them all to me.

121
00:09:34,137 --> 00:09:35,700
Just all of them. Every single one.

122
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,742
- That's more than 40.
- More is better!

123
00:09:37,742 --> 00:09:39,958
- Okay.
- Thank you.

124
00:09:43,018 --> 00:09:44,658
Could you hurry a little, please?

125
00:09:44,658 --> 00:09:46,367
- Okay.
- I'm running late for work.

126
00:09:46,367 --> 00:09:49,533
- Oh, are you sharing at the office?
- No.

127
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,819
I'm eating every last one myself.

128
00:09:51,819 --> 00:09:54,125
Oh, okay...

129
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,742
Oh, hi, PD Shin!

130
00:10:01,742 --> 00:10:02,742
Hi, Writer Kim.

131
00:10:02,742 --> 00:10:04,501
[Bbang-eo Bbang-eo]

132
00:10:04,501 --> 00:10:07,128
What a coincidence seeing you here again!

133
00:10:07,128 --> 00:10:08,325
Yeah, small world.

134
00:10:08,325 --> 00:10:10,867
You're really into bungeoppang, huh?

135
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:12,884
Strawberry Cream Custard ones again?

136
00:10:12,884 --> 00:10:14,344
Yeah.

137
00:10:14,344 --> 00:10:16,096
Wait, seriously?

138
00:10:16,096 --> 00:10:18,515
You might be out of luck.

139
00:10:18,515 --> 00:10:19,867
All set.

140
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:22,750
Thanks so much!

141
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:29,215
Thank you.

142
00:10:29,215 --> 00:10:31,950
All right, done.

143
00:10:31,950 --> 00:10:34,200
- So all of those are...
- Yes.

144
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,408
These are all

145
00:10:36,408 --> 00:10:39,292
Strawberry Cream Custard.

146
00:10:40,169 --> 00:10:42,417
Catch you next week!

147
00:10:45,959 --> 00:10:48,406
Writer Kim...

148
00:10:48,406 --> 00:10:50,333
The bungeoppang...

149
00:10:55,408 --> 00:10:57,492
Hello.

150
00:10:58,742 --> 00:11:00,724
Oh, hello.

151
00:11:00,724 --> 00:11:04,493
If you came for the Strawberry Cream Custard,
sorry, but we're sold out.

152
00:11:04,493 --> 00:11:07,992
I have to make more filling,
so they won't be ready till the afternoon.

153
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:30,333
<i>Right then...</i>

154
00:11:39,242 --> 00:11:41,375
[Endorphin]

155
00:11:42,575 --> 00:11:45,708
<i>It'd been a while since Endorphin showed up.</i>

156
00:11:54,117 --> 00:11:56,492
Coco, did you see that? Did you?

157
00:11:56,492 --> 00:11:59,075
That stunned look on his face.

158
00:11:59,075 --> 00:12:01,533
I got payback for you, Coco.

159
00:12:01,533 --> 00:12:03,542
Pretty good, right?

160
00:12:08,283 --> 00:12:10,542
Oh, that felt so good.

161
00:12:14,950 --> 00:12:17,658
<i>♪ Pissed off? Eat some angry snapper ♪</i>

162
00:12:17,658 --> 00:12:20,117
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

163
00:12:20,117 --> 00:12:22,533
<i>♪ Fired up? Cook some angry snapper ♪</i>

164
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,075
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

165
00:12:25,075 --> 00:12:27,242
All you Cells who love Yumi!

166
00:12:27,242 --> 00:12:29,917
Make a circle over your heads!

167
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:34,658
One, two, three, four!

168
00:12:34,658 --> 00:12:37,825
<i>♪ Let's eat, let's eat, let's eat ♪</i>

169
00:12:37,825 --> 00:12:43,417
<i>♪ Dig into that angry snapper ♪</i>

170
00:12:45,493 --> 00:12:48,583
<i>It was party time again after forever.</i>

171
00:12:53,335 --> 00:12:56,463
What a nice breeze.

172
00:12:56,463 --> 00:12:59,542
Beautiful day, isn't it, Coco?

173
00:13:06,097 --> 00:13:08,950
Who cares how smart a Maltese is?

174
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:11,200
That's not what my writing's about.

175
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:13,563
Would a poodle change the whole theme?

176
00:13:13,563 --> 00:13:15,659
Does it change the male lead at all?

177
00:13:15,659 --> 00:13:18,283
Coco, what's got her so mad?

178
00:13:18,283 --> 00:13:20,533
And then guess what he said?

179
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:22,530
He said Maltese eat poop too.

180
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:26,033
Is he out of his mind or what?

181
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:27,051
Eating poop?

182
00:13:27,051 --> 00:13:29,742
Yeah! He said Maltese eat poop.

183
00:13:29,742 --> 00:13:32,367
As a Maltese owner, isn't that ridiculous?

184
00:13:32,367 --> 00:13:34,209
That's straight-up disrespect.

185
00:13:34,209 --> 00:13:36,458
Disrespect to all of us owners.

186
00:13:38,047 --> 00:13:41,658
Though Coco eats poop, so I can't fight it.

187
00:13:41,658 --> 00:13:42,775
Wait, what?

188
00:13:42,775 --> 00:13:46,304
She licks her own poop sometimes.

189
00:13:46,304 --> 00:13:49,658
No big deal, just brush her teeth.

190
00:13:49,658 --> 00:13:51,958
Isn't that right, Coco?

191
00:13:55,408 --> 00:13:57,367
Hey, by the way,

192
00:13:57,367 --> 00:13:58,993
why do you look so happy?

193
00:13:58,993 --> 00:14:00,700
Me? Happy?

194
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:04,042
You totally are. It's been a while.

195
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:08,331
No, I'm really not cheerful.

196
00:14:08,331 --> 00:14:10,625
I'm just mad.

197
00:14:12,617 --> 00:14:15,500
Why? You're mad too, right?

198
00:14:16,325 --> 00:14:18,158
Oh, right.

199
00:14:26,261 --> 00:14:27,367
Here, take it.

200
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,242
Huh? Is this Bungeoppang?

201
00:14:29,242 --> 00:14:30,950
I never confront people directly.

202
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:33,518
I take revenge gracefully.

203
00:14:33,518 --> 00:14:37,667
That's pro Writer Kim's way with amateurs.

204
00:14:39,013 --> 00:14:41,867
Gracefully, yeah.

205
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:45,783
Bye Coco, let's hang out again, okay?

206
00:14:45,783 --> 00:14:48,617
Thanks so much!
I'll treat you to a meal next week.

207
00:14:48,617 --> 00:14:50,660
Alright, off you go.

208
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:52,658
- Bye.
- Say bye-bye. That's a good girl.

209
00:14:52,658 --> 00:14:55,208
- Bye now.
- Bye.

210
00:15:02,783 --> 00:15:05,658
[Take care of yourself. See you next time]

211
00:15:05,658 --> 00:15:08,033
- Have a safe trip home.
- Have a safe trip home.

212
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,011
<i>- Now the Maltese is leaving too.</i>
- Bye-bye.

213
00:15:10,011 --> 00:15:11,825
<i>Once the angry snapper festival ended,</i>

214
00:15:11,825 --> 00:15:14,750
<i>the village felt empty all over again.</i>

215
00:15:15,851 --> 00:15:18,158
Finally, I can get some work done.

216
00:15:18,158 --> 00:15:20,063
Haven't gotten a word down since yesterday.

217
00:15:20,063 --> 00:15:22,417
It's all Shin Soon Rok's fault.

218
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:48,125
- Yes, who's there?
<i>- It's a delivery.</i>

219
00:15:49,676 --> 00:15:52,000
I didn't order anything.

220
00:15:56,808 --> 00:15:58,792
What is this?

221
00:16:04,491 --> 00:16:07,194
[To Writer Kim, From Shin Soon Rok]

222
00:16:07,194 --> 00:16:09,250
From Shin Soon Rok?

223
00:16:10,572 --> 00:16:12,908
Shin Soon Rok?

224
00:16:12,908 --> 00:16:14,875
What's he up to now?

225
00:16:21,408 --> 00:16:24,586
Soiel Bakery?

226
00:16:24,586 --> 00:16:27,005
No way!

227
00:16:27,005 --> 00:16:29,450
It's Soiel Bakery!

228
00:16:29,450 --> 00:16:33,992
The chef worked at a top 3-star Michelin spot,

229
00:16:33,992 --> 00:16:36,283
famous for seasonal course desserts!

230
00:16:36,283 --> 00:16:38,725
A bakery that's all about desserts!

231
00:16:38,725 --> 00:16:42,283
Money won't even get you a table there!

232
00:16:42,283 --> 00:16:44,242
PD Shin actually sent that?

233
00:16:44,242 --> 00:16:47,292
PD Shin, who wouldn't even share
a single bungeoppang?

234
00:17:11,174 --> 00:17:13,458
Oh, these look so cute!

235
00:17:18,033 --> 00:17:19,933
These are so adorable!

236
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:21,026
Wait a second.

237
00:17:21,026 --> 00:17:23,870
This isn't something
you can get delivered online.

238
00:17:23,870 --> 00:17:26,606
He went there himself to buy and send these.

239
00:17:26,606 --> 00:17:28,075
Bottom line,

240
00:17:28,075 --> 00:17:29,610
this is heartfelt.

241
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:30,992
What's this about?

242
00:17:31,908 --> 00:17:34,030
That spooked him earlier.

243
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:37,083
He realized he slipped up.

244
00:17:39,995 --> 00:17:44,867
Seeing me buy out
all the bungeoppang scared him.

245
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:48,333
Gosh, he's so pathetic it's actually endearing.

246
00:17:49,921 --> 00:17:53,417
These must be amazing.

247
00:17:54,617 --> 00:17:57,250
These are too pretty to eat, honestly.

248
00:18:02,158 --> 00:18:06,147
Maybe shoot him a thank-you message first.

249
00:18:06,147 --> 00:18:07,825
Right, good thinking.

250
00:18:07,825 --> 00:18:10,117
He's not a terrible person or anything.

251
00:18:10,117 --> 00:18:12,527
He was just immature, that's all.

252
00:18:12,527 --> 00:18:14,292
Right.

253
00:18:24,783 --> 00:18:27,075
Who is it this late?

254
00:18:30,325 --> 00:18:32,375
Who's there?

255
00:18:33,242 --> 00:18:36,908
Writer Kim, it's me, PD Shin.

256
00:18:36,908 --> 00:18:38,444
Excuse me?

257
00:18:38,444 --> 00:18:40,117
Why is he here?

258
00:18:40,117 --> 00:18:41,658
Did he come to say sorry?

259
00:18:41,658 --> 00:18:43,700
He sent food and now he's showing up in person?

260
00:18:48,228 --> 00:18:49,730
Oh, PD Shin.

261
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:53,033
Sorry for showing up so late.

262
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:54,484
It's fine.

263
00:18:54,484 --> 00:18:57,792
But what brings you here at this hour?

264
00:18:58,447 --> 00:19:00,750
- Were you maybe...
- I was just thinking about...

265
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:04,703
Sorry?

266
00:19:04,703 --> 00:19:07,539
The dessert I sent...

267
00:19:07,539 --> 00:19:09,158
Oh yeah, I got them.

268
00:19:09,158 --> 00:19:11,492
I was literally just about to message you.

269
00:19:11,492 --> 00:19:15,500
- Oh, they look so delicious...
- Oh, you already tried them.

270
00:19:16,757 --> 00:19:18,417
What?

271
00:19:19,635 --> 00:19:21,750
Got it.

272
00:19:23,513 --> 00:19:24,575
Hold on.

273
00:19:24,575 --> 00:19:26,200
This feels weird again.

274
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,435
Something's not right again, is it?

275
00:19:28,435 --> 00:19:31,647
Oh wait, I think I get it now.

276
00:19:31,647 --> 00:19:33,941
Wait,

277
00:19:33,941 --> 00:19:36,485
did you send this by mistake?

278
00:19:36,485 --> 00:19:39,667
Was it meant for another Writer Kim...

279
00:19:41,281 --> 00:19:42,958
Yeah.

280
00:19:45,369 --> 00:19:46,536
<i>Angry!</i>

281
00:19:46,536 --> 00:19:47,867
<i>Angry! Angry!</i>

282
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:48,867
<i>Angry!</i>

283
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:51,700
<i>- Well now, it's prime time for Angry Snapper.
- Angry!</i>

284
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,367
<i>Angry!</i>

285
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:55,625
<i>Angry!</i>

286
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:00,666
[Episode 5: A Delivery from PD Shin]

287
00:20:01,825 --> 00:20:04,458
<i>There's something called a compliment delivery.</i>

288
00:20:06,765 --> 00:20:08,833
Delivery!

289
00:20:11,658 --> 00:20:13,783
No way, it's a compliment delivery!

290
00:20:13,783 --> 00:20:18,325
<i>Every praise is delivered directly
to the specific cell it's meant for.</i>

291
00:20:18,325 --> 00:20:20,867
<i>These delivery boxes contain a soul...</i>

292
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:23,615
Hi! I'm here to give you something.

293
00:20:23,615 --> 00:20:25,283
No way, it's a present!

294
00:20:25,283 --> 00:20:26,867
This is so exciting!

295
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:30,500
<i>Which then presents a gift to the cell.</i>

296
00:20:31,742 --> 00:20:33,075
Sir.

297
00:20:33,075 --> 00:20:35,877
Here's everything you asked for yesterday.

298
00:20:35,877 --> 00:20:38,542
Oh, thanks. Right.

299
00:20:39,367 --> 00:20:42,833
Man, you never miss a thing.

300
00:20:46,491 --> 00:20:48,825
Compliment delivery for Rational Cell!

301
00:20:48,825 --> 00:20:50,783
No way!

302
00:20:50,783 --> 00:20:52,492
- It's a compliment delivery!
- Here you go.

303
00:20:52,492 --> 00:20:54,408
- Thanks a lot!
<i>- Back in my rookie days,</i>

304
00:20:54,408 --> 00:20:58,708
- Awesome. Time to ask for more focus.
<i>- a single compliment delivery really lifted me.</i>

305
00:21:00,027 --> 00:21:01,867
Hello, Writer Kim.

306
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:04,242
Hey, you're here.

307
00:21:04,242 --> 00:21:07,542
<i>One thing's different now
after all these years.</i>

308
00:21:11,158 --> 00:21:13,867
I didn't have quite enough time,

309
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:17,333
so it's not super detailed yet.

310
00:21:19,033 --> 00:21:21,218
Alright, ship it off to Na Hui.

311
00:21:22,617 --> 00:21:23,950
<i>It's that Yumi has become</i>

312
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:27,375
<i>a person who praises others now.</i>

313
00:21:28,117 --> 00:21:29,492
Good job.

314
00:21:29,492 --> 00:21:30,575
Seriously?

315
00:21:30,575 --> 00:21:33,075
Yeah, this is good.

316
00:21:33,075 --> 00:21:34,908
It's gotten so much better.

317
00:21:34,908 --> 00:21:36,492
Thanks for all the hard work.

318
00:21:36,492 --> 00:21:38,539
I was bracing to get chewed out.

319
00:21:38,539 --> 00:21:40,833
Thanks so much.

320
00:21:44,825 --> 00:21:46,575
But it feels really light.

321
00:21:46,575 --> 00:21:48,367
Isn't this a little half-hearted?

322
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:50,867
You can't mean it every single time.

323
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:53,458
She's been kind of discouraged lately.

324
00:21:54,325 --> 00:21:57,575
Sure, I'll see you tomorrow.

325
00:21:57,575 --> 00:22:00,575
She actually praised me.

326
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:04,273
[It's just a brief idea,
but I'm suggesting it for your review]

327
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:10,417
Why is she not improving at all?

328
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:18,675
<i>Sometimes even hollow praise is necessary,</i>

329
00:22:18,675 --> 00:22:21,542
<i>she figured that out with age.</i>

330
00:22:25,575 --> 00:22:26,992
<i>But...</i>

331
00:22:26,992 --> 00:22:28,710
[Maltese wins dog show]

332
00:22:32,658 --> 00:22:33,992
Shin Soon Rok...

333
00:22:33,992 --> 00:22:37,242
I know exactly what kind of guy you are.

334
00:22:37,242 --> 00:22:39,958
[Winner at the dog show, too!]
Bet he opens the meeting with Maltese talk.

335
00:22:39,958 --> 00:22:41,418
Alright then.

336
00:22:41,418 --> 00:22:43,003
That dog show story was made up.

337
00:22:43,003 --> 00:22:45,714
It was a complete fib,

338
00:22:45,714 --> 00:22:47,758
but I'll find something similar

339
00:22:47,758 --> 00:22:49,934
and send over the link, no matter what.

340
00:22:50,552 --> 00:22:52,262
I mean, with so many competitions out there,

341
00:22:52,262 --> 00:22:54,856
there's got to be a Maltese runner-up.

342
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:57,570
[Most wins at the dog show!]

343
00:23:01,533 --> 00:23:02,855
Oh, hey Na Hui.

344
00:23:02,855 --> 00:23:06,235
Did you read PD Shin's email?

345
00:23:06,235 --> 00:23:08,075
Email? No.

346
00:23:08,075 --> 00:23:11,533
He reached out and mentioned
he sent the script feedback two nights ago.

347
00:23:11,533 --> 00:23:13,617
He noticed you haven't seen it yet

348
00:23:13,617 --> 00:23:17,086
and asked if you could
check it before the meeting.

349
00:23:17,945 --> 00:23:19,623
There's more feedback?

350
00:23:19,623 --> 00:23:21,875
He's still not done with the Maltese thing?

351
00:23:21,875 --> 00:23:25,379
Did PD Shin fight a Maltese
in his past life or what?

352
00:23:25,379 --> 00:23:28,340
<i>I don't really know what it says either.</i>

353
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:30,200
Got it, I'll take a look.

354
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,075
<i>Okay.</i>

355
00:23:33,011 --> 00:23:35,396
Seriously.

356
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:39,658
[Maltese wins dog show]

357
00:23:39,658 --> 00:23:42,104
[Shin Soon Rok]

358
00:23:42,104 --> 00:23:44,798
<i>Writer Kim, it's Shin Soon Rok.</i>

359
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:47,317
<i>Here's some more feedback for you.</i>

360
00:23:47,317 --> 00:23:48,360
[Sent at 02:12]
Seriously?

361
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,745
Two in the morning?

362
00:23:51,492 --> 00:23:54,074
So the Maltese is absolutely off the table?

363
00:23:54,074 --> 00:23:57,117
Important enough to email
at two in the morning?

364
00:23:57,117 --> 00:24:00,200
I've had it with you, Shin Soon Rok.

365
00:24:03,709 --> 00:24:06,033
And why is it this long?

366
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:10,075
He barely talks but writes forever.

367
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:16,471
<i>The thing that caught my eye in this draft</i>

368
00:24:16,471 --> 00:24:19,908
<i>was the way the emotions change.</i>

369
00:24:19,908 --> 00:24:20,934
<i>Like,</i>

370
00:24:20,934 --> 00:24:22,950
<i>"How could someone</i>

371
00:24:22,950 --> 00:24:26,158
<i>- in love be so calm?"</i>
- He gets it.

372
00:24:26,815 --> 00:24:28,025
He really gets it.

373
00:24:28,025 --> 00:24:31,283
He gets exactly what I was going for.

374
00:24:31,943 --> 00:24:34,446
I've been waiting for notes like this.

375
00:24:34,446 --> 00:24:36,747
Yes, exactly!

376
00:24:37,407 --> 00:24:39,284
What?

377
00:24:39,284 --> 00:24:43,121
Since when is he this insightful?

378
00:24:43,121 --> 00:24:45,498
I'm kind of thrown.

379
00:24:45,498 --> 00:24:49,093
<i>I think it'll land as a big turn.</i>

380
00:24:49,961 --> 00:24:52,589
<i>The emotional void in this scene</i>

381
00:24:52,589 --> 00:24:54,591
<i>does more than just explain what's happening.</i>

382
00:24:54,591 --> 00:24:59,854
<i>It makes you reconsider when to end things.</i>

383
00:25:07,729 --> 00:25:10,617
This one's the real deal!

384
00:25:10,617 --> 00:25:14,625
Finally, a compliment delivery from the heart!

385
00:25:15,487 --> 00:25:18,497
- Deliver this to PD Shin.
- Got it.

386
00:25:20,242 --> 00:25:22,917
This kind deserves a reply.

387
00:25:31,252 --> 00:25:35,215
<i>Hi PD Shin, I just read your email.</i>

388
00:25:35,215 --> 00:25:38,218
<i>The feedback's really going to help.</i>

389
00:25:38,218 --> 00:25:39,700
<i>The part I was stuck on is...</i>

390
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:42,075
Hey, where're you going?

391
00:25:43,117 --> 00:25:44,783
You...

392
00:25:50,492 --> 00:25:54,526
[Pride Cell]

393
00:25:54,526 --> 00:25:57,153
When did you wake up?

394
00:25:57,153 --> 00:25:59,242
- Give me that!
- Hey, what's your problem?

395
00:25:59,242 --> 00:26:01,574
No compliments for Shin Soon Rok.

396
00:26:01,574 --> 00:26:05,002
I, Pride Cell, won't allow it!

397
00:26:08,331 --> 00:26:11,042
This is heavy.

398
00:26:11,042 --> 00:26:13,253
Compliment deliveries for Shin Soon Rok

399
00:26:13,253 --> 00:26:16,917
are suspended for now, understand?

400
00:26:18,883 --> 00:26:21,177
Forget it.

401
00:26:21,177 --> 00:26:23,930
[PD Shin]
He did one thing right

402
00:26:23,930 --> 00:26:26,148
and I'm overreacting.

403
00:26:26,891 --> 00:26:28,393
<i>PD Shin,</i>

404
00:26:28,393 --> 00:26:31,153
<i>I've read your email.</i>

405
00:26:34,149 --> 00:26:36,659
A compliment would be wasted on you.

406
00:26:45,283 --> 00:26:47,481
[PD Shin]

407
00:26:49,539 --> 00:26:51,332
Hey, PD Shin.

408
00:26:51,332 --> 00:26:53,126
Hello.

409
00:26:53,126 --> 00:26:54,961
Writer Kim,

410
00:26:54,961 --> 00:26:56,588
you're not at the studio?

411
00:26:56,588 --> 00:26:59,007
I just stepped out.

412
00:26:59,007 --> 00:27:00,425
What's up?

413
00:27:00,425 --> 00:27:01,968
Well...

414
00:27:01,968 --> 00:27:04,470
I came by to give you something.

415
00:27:04,470 --> 00:27:06,306
Then...

416
00:27:06,306 --> 00:27:08,391
I'll leave it with security.

417
00:27:08,391 --> 00:27:11,944
Wait, I'm down at the parking lot.

418
00:27:26,868 --> 00:27:28,328
Oh, PD Shin.

419
00:27:28,328 --> 00:27:30,087
Hello.

420
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:33,642
What brings you here unannounced?

421
00:27:35,084 --> 00:27:37,587
Just wanted to drop this off.

422
00:27:37,587 --> 00:27:39,881
What is it?

423
00:27:39,881 --> 00:27:42,217
This is the same dessert as yesterday.

424
00:27:42,217 --> 00:27:43,343
Oh my.

425
00:27:43,343 --> 00:27:45,011
I'm sorry about yesterday.

426
00:27:45,011 --> 00:27:48,765
Writer Kim Ju Ho specifically asked for it.

427
00:27:48,765 --> 00:27:52,276
Oh, these things happen.

428
00:27:53,102 --> 00:27:55,612
You didn't have to...

429
00:27:56,658 --> 00:27:59,192
Yes, dessert!

430
00:27:59,192 --> 00:28:02,201
Yes, dessert!

431
00:28:02,201 --> 00:28:05,950
Three Michelin-star dessert!

432
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:09,744
I've wanted this so bad!

433
00:28:09,744 --> 00:28:12,247
Smooth move, PD Shin.

434
00:28:12,247 --> 00:28:13,831
Deliver this to PD Shin.

435
00:28:13,831 --> 00:28:16,602
Put my whole heart into it.

436
00:28:17,408 --> 00:28:19,242
Okay, I got it.

437
00:28:25,117 --> 00:28:28,575
What?

438
00:28:28,575 --> 00:28:31,808
Hey! Where are you going now?

439
00:28:31,808 --> 00:28:34,602
Hungry Cell really wants this sent.

440
00:28:34,602 --> 00:28:35,742
I, Pride Cell,

441
00:28:35,742 --> 00:28:38,575
still don't allow it!

442
00:28:42,075 --> 00:28:43,742
I'm really...

443
00:28:45,738 --> 00:28:48,992
This is so heavy.

444
00:28:48,992 --> 00:28:51,953
This wasn't necessary,

445
00:28:51,953 --> 00:28:53,158
but thanks, I'll enjoy it.

446
00:28:53,158 --> 00:28:54,205
Okay.

447
00:28:54,205 --> 00:28:56,965
See you on meeting day.

448
00:29:00,700 --> 00:29:02,030
<i>Give him a ride, at least.</i>

449
00:29:02,030 --> 00:29:04,742
<i>That much, I, Pride Cell, allow.</i>

450
00:29:04,742 --> 00:29:06,950
Where are you going?

451
00:29:09,595 --> 00:29:11,764
Headed to the publisher.

452
00:29:11,764 --> 00:29:14,075
- Let me drop you off.
- No, I'm fine.

453
00:29:14,075 --> 00:29:15,117
Get in.

454
00:29:15,117 --> 00:29:18,992
I'm heading to the publisher to see the editor.

455
00:29:19,783 --> 00:29:21,783
Come on, get in.

456
00:29:21,783 --> 00:29:23,834
Okay.

457
00:29:34,745 --> 00:29:36,455
Let's head out.

458
00:29:36,455 --> 00:29:38,381
Sure.

459
00:29:43,242 --> 00:29:46,700
She shouldn't have offered him a ride.

460
00:29:49,158 --> 00:29:51,804
- How come?
- I'm so anxious.

461
00:29:51,804 --> 00:29:54,473
The publisher's like 20 minutes away.

462
00:29:54,473 --> 00:29:56,976
What are they supposed to talk about?

463
00:29:56,976 --> 00:29:58,992
PD Shin's not gonna talk.

464
00:29:58,992 --> 00:30:00,242
What then?

465
00:30:00,242 --> 00:30:03,816
They're going the same way.
She can't bail on him.

466
00:30:03,816 --> 00:30:07,285
She could die from how awkward this is.

467
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:10,614
This isn't going to work.

468
00:30:10,614 --> 00:30:13,666
- Reaction No. 1!
- Yes!

469
00:30:24,211 --> 00:30:26,762
Hey, Reaction No. 1, what're you doing?

470
00:30:27,464 --> 00:30:29,758
Looking through the chat list.

471
00:30:29,758 --> 00:30:32,268
Hold on a second.

472
00:30:34,367 --> 00:30:36,579
It's already silent.

473
00:30:36,579 --> 00:30:38,908
What do they do?

474
00:30:38,908 --> 00:30:40,310
Let's play music.

475
00:30:40,310 --> 00:30:42,611
That way they can stop talking.

476
00:30:51,655 --> 00:30:55,825
Any music you're into?

477
00:30:55,825 --> 00:30:58,203
Not really, no.

478
00:30:58,203 --> 00:31:00,242
Oh, okay.

479
00:31:00,242 --> 00:31:03,158
Then...

480
00:31:03,158 --> 00:31:04,408
Hey, there's a car!

481
00:31:04,408 --> 00:31:06,202
Oh my!

482
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:09,839
What's wrong with that car?

483
00:31:09,839 --> 00:31:11,325
Why's he coming in the exit?

484
00:31:11,325 --> 00:31:13,575
What's up with him?

485
00:31:14,511 --> 00:31:17,222
Writer Kim, you came in the wrong way.

486
00:31:17,222 --> 00:31:18,974
What?

487
00:31:18,974 --> 00:31:20,733
Look over there.

488
00:31:21,325 --> 00:31:22,386
What?

489
00:31:22,386 --> 00:31:25,206
- Oh, what do I do?
- Hey, what're you doing?

490
00:31:30,443 --> 00:31:32,158
Oh no, what now?

491
00:31:32,158 --> 00:31:34,200
- No...
- You should back up first.

492
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,240
Back it up.

493
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:37,104
A bit further back should do it.

494
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:38,660
Right, reverse.

495
00:31:38,660 --> 00:31:41,788
Reverse...

496
00:31:41,788 --> 00:31:43,964
- Let me help you.
- Sure.

497
00:31:48,216 --> 00:31:49,283
Stop!

498
00:31:49,283 --> 00:31:50,658
Watch the right side!

499
00:31:50,658 --> 00:31:52,632
Try going forward first.

500
00:31:52,632 --> 00:31:55,476
- And then reverse.
- Got it.

501
00:31:58,638 --> 00:32:01,117
Wheel to the right.

502
00:32:01,117 --> 00:32:02,600
Stop there.

503
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,652
Go ahead and reverse now.

504
00:32:06,367 --> 00:32:08,992
- Just keep backing up.
- Got it.

505
00:32:08,992 --> 00:32:11,234
Slowly crank the wheel to the right.

506
00:32:11,234 --> 00:32:13,285
To the right?

507
00:32:14,946 --> 00:32:16,951
Stop there!

508
00:32:20,476 --> 00:32:22,992
How about I take over?

509
00:32:22,992 --> 00:32:25,625
Yeah, that sounds good.

510
00:32:29,906 --> 00:32:30,950
Writer Kim?

511
00:32:30,950 --> 00:32:32,992
Step out, please.

512
00:32:35,626 --> 00:32:38,727
I can't really get out though...

513
00:32:39,325 --> 00:32:41,899
- Come out this way.
- Okay.

514
00:32:46,033 --> 00:32:47,533
Hold on.

515
00:32:47,533 --> 00:32:49,543
Thank you.

516
00:32:52,275 --> 00:32:54,205
Get in.

517
00:33:40,407 --> 00:33:43,867
PD Shin's a good driver.

518
00:33:43,867 --> 00:33:47,458
What a relief.

519
00:33:58,631 --> 00:34:01,176
- What're you doing?
- I'm sorry.

520
00:34:01,176 --> 00:34:03,102
I'm sorry.

521
00:34:06,598 --> 00:34:09,525
Gosh, he scared me.

522
00:34:11,019 --> 00:34:13,188
Let's grab a cab.

523
00:34:13,188 --> 00:34:14,981
I'll handle the parking.

524
00:34:14,981 --> 00:34:16,566
Yeah, that works.

525
00:34:16,566 --> 00:34:18,693
I got so startled too...

526
00:34:18,693 --> 00:34:20,766
Okay.

527
00:34:36,617 --> 00:34:39,589
I was really on edge.

528
00:34:39,589 --> 00:34:43,968
What would she do without PD Shin?

529
00:34:43,968 --> 00:34:46,742
Take this as a rush delivery.

530
00:34:46,742 --> 00:34:47,867
Got it.

531
00:34:57,482 --> 00:35:00,283
Hey, where to this time?

532
00:35:02,742 --> 00:35:04,906
It's a rush job.

533
00:35:04,906 --> 00:35:06,366
Not happening!

534
00:35:06,366 --> 00:35:08,034
My pride still won't allow...

535
00:35:08,034 --> 00:35:09,535
You're still at it?

536
00:35:09,535 --> 00:35:12,908
It's only polite to compliment him.

537
00:35:12,908 --> 00:35:16,125
Don't let pride wreck Yumi's manners!

538
00:35:16,125 --> 00:35:18,033
Manners Cell, good job.

539
00:35:18,033 --> 00:35:20,296
Hurry, deliver it! Go, go!

540
00:35:20,296 --> 00:35:22,257
Okay!

541
00:35:22,257 --> 00:35:25,476
Go!

542
00:35:34,867 --> 00:35:37,283
I'll call a taxi.

543
00:35:37,283 --> 00:35:39,658
Thank you so much.

544
00:35:40,867 --> 00:35:43,617
You drive really well.

545
00:35:43,617 --> 00:35:44,946
It's nothing.

546
00:35:44,946 --> 00:35:46,274
No, really.

547
00:35:46,274 --> 00:35:49,867
What if you hadn't been there?

548
00:35:49,867 --> 00:35:52,075
That was such a mess.

549
00:35:52,075 --> 00:35:55,915
How long have you been driving?

550
00:35:55,915 --> 00:35:57,764
Well...

551
00:35:57,764 --> 00:36:00,977
About six months since I started again.

552
00:36:00,977 --> 00:36:02,547
Six months?

553
00:36:02,547 --> 00:36:04,223
Yes.

554
00:36:14,992 --> 00:36:16,769
- Who's there?
- Who is it?

555
00:36:16,769 --> 00:36:19,658
Hi, I'm from Soon Rok's village.

556
00:36:19,658 --> 00:36:22,158
I've got a delivery.

557
00:36:26,742 --> 00:36:29,492
Soon Rok sent a delivery too.

558
00:36:29,492 --> 00:36:31,700
- What is it?
- I hope it's nice.

559
00:36:31,700 --> 00:36:34,783
This could help them get closer.

560
00:36:36,038 --> 00:36:37,331
What's this?

561
00:36:37,331 --> 00:36:39,708
<i>- Not every delivery is a compliment.</i>
- What is that?

562
00:36:39,708 --> 00:36:41,251
It's totally blank.

563
00:36:41,251 --> 00:36:42,783
Why's the paper empty?

564
00:36:42,783 --> 00:36:44,283
Wait a second.

565
00:36:44,283 --> 00:36:47,375
It's not empty.

566
00:36:48,992 --> 00:36:52,533
Wait, there's a secret message.

567
00:36:52,533 --> 00:36:54,620
A secret code?

568
00:36:57,684 --> 00:37:00,145
Look, it's showing up!

569
00:37:00,145 --> 00:37:03,065
- "Quit"
- "Quit"

570
00:37:03,065 --> 00:37:05,525
- "driving"
- "driving"

571
00:37:05,525 --> 00:37:07,194
- "already."
- "already."

572
00:37:07,194 --> 00:37:10,329
<i>Some deliveries are silent mockery.</i>

573
00:37:12,698 --> 00:37:15,131
[Quit driving already]

574
00:37:17,829 --> 00:37:21,507
- Quit driving already.
- Quit driving already.

575
00:37:25,712 --> 00:37:27,369
<i>Whoever gets this delivery</i>

576
00:37:27,369 --> 00:37:29,992
<i>- feels upset for no reason.</i>
- That jerk...

577
00:37:29,992 --> 00:37:33,075
<i>They feel completely insulted.</i>

578
00:37:42,062 --> 00:37:44,158
That was fast.

579
00:37:44,158 --> 00:37:46,658
<i>Going up.</i>

580
00:37:49,236 --> 00:37:51,579
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

581
00:37:52,197 --> 00:37:53,956
Writer Kim?

582
00:38:03,158 --> 00:38:05,739
[Episode 6: Time for a Change]

583
00:38:08,797 --> 00:38:11,133
Hey, Fishing Cell.

584
00:38:11,133 --> 00:38:13,926
- Yeah?
- Got another angry snapper today?

585
00:38:13,926 --> 00:38:17,221
If every day were like this, I'd be set.

586
00:38:17,221 --> 00:38:21,267
PD Shin deserves a thank-you gift.

587
00:38:21,267 --> 00:38:22,533
Rational Cell.

588
00:38:22,533 --> 00:38:24,729
I'm freaking out again.

589
00:38:24,729 --> 00:38:26,856
Seriously, what's wrong now?

590
00:38:26,856 --> 00:38:28,357
I'm so nervous.

591
00:38:28,357 --> 00:38:32,361
She's got Busan tomorrow, needs sleep.

592
00:38:32,361 --> 00:38:36,581
What if she misses the train?

593
00:38:39,035 --> 00:38:41,336
Really.

594
00:38:45,583 --> 00:38:47,884
Seriously.

595
00:38:49,850 --> 00:38:54,367
She's still wide awake.

596
00:38:54,367 --> 00:38:57,094
She'd sleep if you stopped panicking.

597
00:38:57,094 --> 00:38:59,055
So hungry!

598
00:38:59,055 --> 00:39:00,514
Let's eat something!

599
00:39:00,514 --> 00:39:02,433
Let's have a midnight snack!

600
00:39:02,433 --> 00:39:04,901
What's wrong with you?

601
00:39:06,979 --> 00:39:09,232
I'm starving.

602
00:39:09,232 --> 00:39:11,908
I'm hungry.

603
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:25,847
Yumi, let's eat the 3-star dessert.

604
00:39:25,847 --> 00:39:27,416
Come on, let's eat it.

605
00:39:27,416 --> 00:39:31,178
I've been craving it for a while.

606
00:39:35,825 --> 00:39:37,575
Forget it, I won't touch it.

607
00:39:37,575 --> 00:39:40,075
I'd rather eat my bungeoppang.

608
00:39:53,742 --> 00:39:56,283
Because of that guy, I keep snacking.

609
00:39:56,283 --> 00:39:58,492
My blood sugar's dropping.

610
00:40:11,575 --> 00:40:15,555
<i>How long have you been driving?</i>

611
00:40:18,050 --> 00:40:20,636
Come on, I'm still learning.

612
00:40:20,636 --> 00:40:24,306
He reversed once and looked at me like that?

613
00:40:24,306 --> 00:40:27,242
Unbelievable.

614
00:40:27,242 --> 00:40:29,227
[Quit driving already]

615
00:40:29,227 --> 00:40:32,814
Told you not to send that package.

616
00:40:32,814 --> 00:40:35,399
You sent it on your own, your fault!

617
00:40:35,399 --> 00:40:39,028
I didn't know he had zero manners.

618
00:40:39,028 --> 00:40:42,240
I want dessert!

619
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,283
Let's eat dessert!

620
00:40:44,283 --> 00:40:46,905
- Hey! Have some pride, please!
- Dessert!

621
00:40:46,905 --> 00:40:51,708
- You'd eat his charity dessert now?
- I want dessert!

622
00:40:52,416 --> 00:40:56,367
But I want it!

623
00:40:56,367 --> 00:41:00,091
Dessert!

624
00:41:00,091 --> 00:41:01,950
Guys, aren't you going to bed?

625
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:04,356
- Dessert!
- When am I supposed to work?

626
00:41:04,356 --> 00:41:05,388
Hey.

627
00:41:05,388 --> 00:41:07,765
We hired PD Shin to help me write.

628
00:41:07,765 --> 00:41:09,433
Not to piss me off every day!

629
00:41:09,433 --> 00:41:12,937
Can't get a moment of peace here!

630
00:41:12,937 --> 00:41:14,147
Calm down.

631
00:41:14,147 --> 00:41:16,907
She'll adjust to him eventually.

632
00:41:17,859 --> 00:41:20,236
No, swap him out.

633
00:41:20,236 --> 00:41:22,075
Swap him out?

634
00:41:22,075 --> 00:41:25,241
Tell Editor An we want a new PD.

635
00:41:25,241 --> 00:41:29,495
If he's in the way, he must be removed.

636
00:41:29,495 --> 00:41:31,164
Should I

637
00:41:31,164 --> 00:41:33,291
just ask for a new PD?

638
00:41:33,291 --> 00:41:35,668
You see Editor An in Busan tomorrow.

639
00:41:35,668 --> 00:41:39,422
No PD Shin around. It's the perfect time.

640
00:41:39,422 --> 00:41:42,133
Didn't you say his feedback was useful?

641
00:41:42,133 --> 00:41:44,427
If I can't write just to get his notes,

642
00:41:44,427 --> 00:41:45,970
I'd rather skip it completely.

643
00:41:45,970 --> 00:41:48,306
That might really be the better choice.

644
00:41:48,306 --> 00:41:50,308
Shin Soon Rok, the pain in the neck,

645
00:41:50,308 --> 00:41:52,018
isn't going to change anytime soon.

646
00:41:52,018 --> 00:41:53,227
Exactly my point.

647
00:41:53,227 --> 00:41:55,605
All right, let's say she meets him.

648
00:41:55,605 --> 00:41:57,398
Then what does she tell him?

649
00:41:57,398 --> 00:41:59,066
So...

650
00:41:59,066 --> 00:42:03,779
You're saying kick PD Shin out?

651
00:42:03,779 --> 00:42:05,781
Yeah.

652
00:42:05,781 --> 00:42:07,950
Sure, understood.

653
00:42:07,950 --> 00:42:10,828
If he's no help to your work, he's out.

654
00:42:10,828 --> 00:42:11,996
But...

655
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:14,123
could you tell me

656
00:42:14,123 --> 00:42:16,325
what specifically bothered you?

657
00:42:16,325 --> 00:42:19,575
Oh, well...

658
00:42:20,171 --> 00:42:23,765
He called Maltese dogs stupid.

659
00:42:24,383 --> 00:42:27,436
Because he called Maltese dogs stupid?

660
00:42:28,763 --> 00:42:30,431
Is that really a reason to replace him?

661
00:42:30,431 --> 00:42:33,184
That sounds kind of petty.

662
00:42:33,184 --> 00:42:36,437
He took all eight Strawberry Cream

663
00:42:36,437 --> 00:42:39,649
Custard Bungeoppang I love, and it upset me...

664
00:42:39,649 --> 00:42:42,902
Over eight Strawberry Cream Bungeoppang?

665
00:42:42,902 --> 00:42:45,363
Gosh, that's pretty petty too.

666
00:42:45,363 --> 00:42:47,748
Bungeoppang? Really?

667
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:50,993
We rode the bus together,

668
00:42:50,993 --> 00:42:54,705
and he just put his earphones on alone.

669
00:42:54,705 --> 00:42:55,998
Over earphones?

670
00:42:55,998 --> 00:42:59,617
Gosh, that's super petty!

671
00:42:59,617 --> 00:43:01,818
He laughed at me

672
00:43:01,818 --> 00:43:03,756
for being a bad driver.

673
00:43:03,756 --> 00:43:06,892
He was definitely laughing at me.

674
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:10,137
His face,

675
00:43:10,137 --> 00:43:12,098
it was exactly like this!

676
00:43:12,098 --> 00:43:13,891
No way!

677
00:43:13,891 --> 00:43:18,236
This is way too petty!

678
00:43:21,033 --> 00:43:23,651
No.

679
00:43:23,651 --> 00:43:26,362
There's no real reason to replace him.

680
00:43:26,362 --> 00:43:28,663
No justification.

681
00:43:29,492 --> 00:43:32,285
These reasons are just lame.

682
00:43:32,285 --> 00:43:35,045
I'll only embarrass myself.

683
00:43:36,700 --> 00:43:38,867
But

684
00:43:38,867 --> 00:43:41,492
the lame reasons make me even madder.

685
00:43:44,171 --> 00:43:46,765
Why am I so annoyed?

686
00:43:48,450 --> 00:43:51,887
Come on, let's calm down.

687
00:43:51,887 --> 00:43:54,682
A trip to Busan will clear your mind,

688
00:43:54,682 --> 00:43:57,742
and you may see it differently.

689
00:43:57,742 --> 00:44:00,575
Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.

690
00:44:00,575 --> 00:44:05,318
- Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.
- Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.

691
00:44:05,318 --> 00:44:07,037
Yeah, let's do that.

692
00:44:07,037 --> 00:44:09,325
I'll decide when I get back.

693
00:44:09,325 --> 00:44:11,832
Why am I even stressing over him?

694
00:44:49,158 --> 00:44:51,185
9 a.m.

695
00:44:51,185 --> 00:44:53,957
I'm here a bit early.

696
00:44:55,367 --> 00:44:59,367
<i>Hi PD Jang, I made it.</i>

697
00:45:05,293 --> 00:45:07,628
Rational Cell,

698
00:45:07,628 --> 00:45:10,089
something's bugging me.

699
00:45:10,089 --> 00:45:11,883
What are you worried about now?

700
00:45:11,883 --> 00:45:12,992
You know,

701
00:45:12,992 --> 00:45:15,742
what if PD Jang suddenly can't make it

702
00:45:15,742 --> 00:45:20,075
and PD Shin shows up instead?

703
00:45:20,950 --> 00:45:23,895
- What would she do then?
- Hey!

704
00:45:23,895 --> 00:45:26,147
Quit saying horrible stuff like that!

705
00:45:26,147 --> 00:45:30,033
Take the train to Busan with that guy?

706
00:45:30,033 --> 00:45:32,111
For that many hours?

707
00:45:32,111 --> 00:45:35,367
Yumi seriously couldn't breathe.

708
00:45:35,367 --> 00:45:39,617
She could die!

709
00:45:50,755 --> 00:45:53,466
- Hi, PD Jang.
<i>- Writer Kim!</i>

710
00:45:53,466 --> 00:45:54,592
Where are you?

711
00:45:54,592 --> 00:45:55,968
What do I do?

712
00:45:55,968 --> 00:45:57,553
Something happened.

713
00:45:57,553 --> 00:45:59,867
My younger sister's having early labor,

714
00:45:59,867 --> 00:46:01,432
and nobody's home right now.

715
00:46:01,432 --> 00:46:03,392
I need to go with her.

716
00:46:03,392 --> 00:46:05,102
Oh my, that's terrible.

717
00:46:05,102 --> 00:46:08,105
So I asked PD Shin to go instead.

718
00:46:08,105 --> 00:46:09,533
PD Shin?

719
00:46:09,533 --> 00:46:11,367
I knew it!

720
00:46:11,367 --> 00:46:14,654
I said I was worried!

721
00:46:14,654 --> 00:46:18,032
<i>He just left, but he may run a little late.</i>

722
00:46:18,032 --> 00:46:19,951
Wait,

723
00:46:19,951 --> 00:46:24,478
am I traveling with PD Shin?

724
00:46:24,478 --> 00:46:26,367
Yes, why don't you get on first?

725
00:46:26,367 --> 00:46:30,253
He can take the next train if he's late.

726
00:46:30,253 --> 00:46:32,380
Oh, sure.

727
00:46:32,380 --> 00:46:34,556
Yes, understood.

728
00:46:39,117 --> 00:46:41,742
Come on, be late, please be late.

729
00:46:42,682 --> 00:46:44,983
Don't come!

730
00:47:13,087 --> 00:47:15,214
<i>Good morning, passengers.</i>

731
00:47:15,214 --> 00:47:18,759
<i>This is the express train to Busan Station.</i>

732
00:47:18,759 --> 00:47:21,679
<i>Our crew will do everything we can</i>

733
00:47:21,679 --> 00:47:23,555
<i>to make your ride pleasant.</i>

734
00:47:23,555 --> 00:47:27,100
<i>No way I can ride with Shin Soon Rok.</i>

735
00:47:27,100 --> 00:47:29,269
<i>How do I put up with that awkwardness?</i>

736
00:47:29,269 --> 00:47:32,196
<i>Even seeing his face bugs me.</i>

737
00:47:35,192 --> 00:47:38,786
<i>Come on, be late. It's better that way.</i>

738
00:47:40,117 --> 00:47:41,648
[Busan]

739
00:47:49,623 --> 00:47:51,549
Train's moving.

740
00:48:03,428 --> 00:48:07,857
- Hurray! We're saved!
- Hurray!

741
00:48:12,646 --> 00:48:16,399
Is this really something to celebrate?

742
00:48:16,399 --> 00:48:18,409
We're supposed to be a team...

743
00:48:19,152 --> 00:48:21,746
Oh, I don't care.

744
00:48:30,617 --> 00:48:32,575
Writer Kim.

745
00:48:53,853 --> 00:48:57,198
I barely made the train.

746
00:48:58,950 --> 00:49:00,533
You heard about it, right?

747
00:49:00,533 --> 00:49:03,532
I'm going with you instead.

748
00:49:03,532 --> 00:49:05,198
Oh, right.

749
00:49:05,198 --> 00:49:07,833
Oh, sure.

750
00:49:08,658 --> 00:49:10,996
So, you made it on?

751
00:49:10,996 --> 00:49:12,497
Yeah,

752
00:49:12,497 --> 00:49:14,666
I had to run.

753
00:49:14,666 --> 00:49:17,408
Oh, you had to run.

754
00:49:17,408 --> 00:49:21,408
Oh, good thing we're going together.

755
00:49:22,881 --> 00:49:24,967
You usually wear glasses, right?

756
00:49:24,967 --> 00:49:27,761
Yeah, I left them behind.

757
00:49:27,761 --> 00:49:30,021
I see.

758
00:49:30,889 --> 00:49:33,267
Without glasses, he seems like someone else.

759
00:49:33,267 --> 00:49:35,829
Yeah, and his hair's down in front.

760
00:49:37,479 --> 00:49:39,690
Everyone, no time for gossip.

761
00:49:39,690 --> 00:49:41,108
Red alert!

762
00:49:41,108 --> 00:49:43,658
Okay, everyone get ready.

763
00:49:43,658 --> 00:49:44,945
Especially you, Reaction No. 1!

764
00:49:44,945 --> 00:49:47,072
- Stay sharp.
- Got it!

765
00:49:47,072 --> 00:49:49,575
Emotion Cell, Pride Cell, stay calm.

766
00:49:49,575 --> 00:49:51,577
You've got Cursing Cell locked up, right?

767
00:49:51,577 --> 00:49:53,245
Don't let her say a word.

768
00:49:53,245 --> 00:49:56,915
Manners Cell,
stay chill if he puts earphones on.

769
00:49:56,915 --> 00:49:58,071
- Hungry Cell!
- Yeah?

770
00:49:58,071 --> 00:50:01,093
Be ready if he eats snacks by himself.

771
00:50:02,588 --> 00:50:04,783
It's two and a half hours to Busan.

772
00:50:05,533 --> 00:50:07,801
We just need to hold on for that long.

773
00:50:07,801 --> 00:50:08,844
When we're in Busan,

774
00:50:08,844 --> 00:50:11,638
the super friendly Editor An is waiting.

775
00:50:11,638 --> 00:50:14,065
- We got this!
- Right!

776
00:50:14,725 --> 00:50:18,278
Great, going alone would've been dull.

777
00:50:18,278 --> 00:50:19,313
Please sit down.

778
00:50:19,313 --> 00:50:22,858
No, my seat is over there.

779
00:50:22,858 --> 00:50:24,860
Oh, is that so?

780
00:50:24,860 --> 00:50:26,987
They didn't have a seat next to yours.

781
00:50:26,987 --> 00:50:29,038
Got it.

782
00:50:29,865 --> 00:50:34,286
- He's sitting somewhere else!
- He's not sitting with us!

783
00:50:34,286 --> 00:50:36,246
See you when we arrive.

784
00:50:36,246 --> 00:50:37,996
Sure.

785
00:50:51,011 --> 00:50:53,229
Oh, thank goodness.

786
00:50:58,894 --> 00:51:00,854
All right, emergency's over.

787
00:51:00,854 --> 00:51:04,274
Get some rest until we reach Busan.

788
00:51:04,274 --> 00:51:05,646
Hold on.

789
00:51:05,646 --> 00:51:07,617
This seems weird.

790
00:51:07,617 --> 00:51:11,600
You think he sat apart on purpose?

791
00:51:11,600 --> 00:51:13,533
Because he didn't want to sit with Yumi.

792
00:51:13,533 --> 00:51:15,950
- What?
- What?

793
00:51:19,158 --> 00:51:21,908
Look how many empty seats there are.

794
00:51:21,908 --> 00:51:24,158
Doesn't that feel weird?

795
00:51:26,617 --> 00:51:28,533
So many empty seats around,

796
00:51:28,533 --> 00:51:31,825
he chose the farthest seat?

797
00:51:33,325 --> 00:51:35,931
He actually sat far away on purpose?

798
00:51:35,931 --> 00:51:39,017
If that's the case, I'm not letting it slide.

799
00:51:39,017 --> 00:51:42,020
No way, it can't be.

800
00:51:42,020 --> 00:51:45,357
If that's real, it's outrageous.

801
00:51:45,357 --> 00:51:48,618
I'm the one holding back here!

802
00:51:57,359 --> 00:51:58,658
Hello?

803
00:51:58,658 --> 00:52:00,831
<i>Hey, Writer Kim, traveling okay?</i>

804
00:52:00,831 --> 00:52:02,450
Yes, I boarded a little bit ago.

805
00:52:02,450 --> 00:52:04,667
<i>I heard something came up for PD Jang.</i>

806
00:52:04,667 --> 00:52:07,461
Right, so I'm going with PD Shin.

807
00:52:07,461 --> 00:52:08,713
Right, I was told.

808
00:52:08,713 --> 00:52:11,424
I've got work, I'll come down later.

809
00:52:11,424 --> 00:52:13,634
Let's grab dinner tonight.

810
00:52:13,634 --> 00:52:16,012
<i>Sounds good.</i>

811
00:52:16,012 --> 00:52:17,847
Well...

812
00:52:17,847 --> 00:52:20,016
The thing is,

813
00:52:20,016 --> 00:52:22,810
so, about PD Shin.

814
00:52:22,810 --> 00:52:24,103
<i>Okay.</i>

815
00:52:24,103 --> 00:52:26,731
Is he with you? I can call you back.

816
00:52:26,731 --> 00:52:31,034
No, our seats are separate, he's far away.

817
00:52:32,111 --> 00:52:35,455
So regarding PD Shin...

818
00:52:36,616 --> 00:52:37,950
What now?

819
00:52:37,950 --> 00:52:39,827
Why's he dragging it out like this?

820
00:52:39,827 --> 00:52:42,997
I'm already nervous.

821
00:52:42,997 --> 00:52:46,417
It's only been a few days since he joined,

822
00:52:46,417 --> 00:52:48,461
so I just wanted to check,

823
00:52:48,461 --> 00:52:52,222
is it all right if we reassign him?

824
00:52:54,383 --> 00:52:57,700
Reassign? So you're...

825
00:52:57,700 --> 00:53:01,242
swapping the PD out?

826
00:53:04,617 --> 00:53:08,908
Right, if you don't mind, can we swap him?

827
00:53:15,571 --> 00:53:17,299
Make some noise!

828
00:53:19,158 --> 00:53:22,578
Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!

829
00:53:22,578 --> 00:53:26,117
- Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!
- Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!

830
00:53:26,117 --> 00:53:28,617
Oh, sure,

831
00:53:29,627 --> 00:53:31,545
I'm fine

832
00:53:31,545 --> 00:53:32,797
with that.

833
00:53:32,797 --> 00:53:34,757
Really? You don't mind?

834
00:53:34,757 --> 00:53:36,514
It is a bit of a shame,

835
00:53:36,514 --> 00:53:37,575
but...

836
00:53:37,575 --> 00:53:40,763
we just started working together,

837
00:53:40,763 --> 00:53:43,283
so it won't really set things back.

838
00:53:43,283 --> 00:53:44,908
Oh, that's a relief.

839
00:53:44,908 --> 00:53:46,811
Thanks for understanding.

840
00:53:46,811 --> 00:53:47,908
No problem.

841
00:53:47,908 --> 00:53:51,075
I'll look for another solid PD for you.

842
00:53:51,075 --> 00:53:53,575
All right, see you there.

843
00:53:53,575 --> 00:53:56,742
Yes, see you later.

844
00:54:01,032 --> 00:54:04,619
Is it really working out this easily?

845
00:54:04,619 --> 00:54:06,370
Perfect timing.

846
00:54:06,370 --> 00:54:08,790
He's out without her saying anything petty.

847
00:54:08,790 --> 00:54:10,450
Good thing she held back.

848
00:54:10,450 --> 00:54:12,085
Patience really does pay off.

849
00:54:12,085 --> 00:54:15,995
Finally, I can focus on writing.

850
00:54:18,132 --> 00:54:19,766
Wait.

851
00:54:20,468 --> 00:54:24,688
So this trip is my last one with him?

852
00:54:26,057 --> 00:54:27,867
Oh my.

853
00:54:27,867 --> 00:54:30,763
Now I'm actually enjoying this ride.

854
00:54:47,495 --> 00:54:49,713
<i>Please insert your card.</i>

855
00:55:02,218 --> 00:55:04,561
Why not, I'm in a good mood.

856
00:55:19,235 --> 00:55:20,575
Here, drink this while you work.

857
00:55:20,575 --> 00:55:23,127
Oh, thank you.

858
00:55:28,077 --> 00:55:31,505
I just talked to Editor An.

859
00:55:33,291 --> 00:55:36,127
We just started, and already it's goodbye.

860
00:55:36,127 --> 00:55:37,170
Right?

861
00:55:37,170 --> 00:55:38,921
Guess we need a farewell party.

862
00:55:38,921 --> 00:55:40,590
I'll miss working with you.

863
00:55:40,590 --> 00:55:41,783
I'm sorry.

864
00:55:41,783 --> 00:55:43,551
You've got nothing to be sorry for...

865
00:55:43,551 --> 00:55:46,770
Thank you for understanding.

866
00:55:52,533 --> 00:55:55,542
Go ahead and answer it.

867
00:55:57,690 --> 00:55:59,616
Hello?

868
00:56:00,776 --> 00:56:03,328
Yeah, I just left.

869
00:56:04,700 --> 00:56:06,449
Something feels off.

870
00:56:06,449 --> 00:56:08,034
Totally off.

871
00:56:08,034 --> 00:56:10,252
Let's check it out.

872
00:56:21,547 --> 00:56:22,715
Hi, Writer Kim.

873
00:56:22,715 --> 00:56:24,300
Hi, Editor An.

874
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:26,552
I've got a question.

875
00:56:26,552 --> 00:56:29,283
Why are you swapping him all of a sudden?

876
00:56:29,283 --> 00:56:30,348
<i>Sorry?</i>

877
00:56:30,348 --> 00:56:33,033
Did PD Shin ask for it, by any chance...

878
00:56:33,033 --> 00:56:37,438
Oh, he already told you?

879
00:56:37,438 --> 00:56:39,742
Juggling it with his other work was hard,

880
00:56:39,742 --> 00:56:43,033
so he wants to focus on just one project.

881
00:56:45,863 --> 00:56:48,915
<i>Seems it was overwhelming him.</i>

882
00:56:50,701 --> 00:56:52,328
What the heck?

883
00:56:52,328 --> 00:56:57,007
So he's the one who wanted out?

884
00:56:58,617 --> 00:57:01,712
Yumi was holding back this whole time.

885
00:57:01,712 --> 00:57:04,533
Now he's the one leaving?

886
00:57:04,533 --> 00:57:06,509
If anyone's dumping anyone, it's Yumi!

887
00:57:06,509 --> 00:57:09,936
Who's he to drop Yumi?

888
00:57:30,158 --> 00:57:32,801
This is killing me!

889
00:57:33,452 --> 00:57:35,579
He's leaving anyway.

890
00:57:35,579 --> 00:57:38,908
He's leaving even if you hold back. Let it out!

891
00:57:38,908 --> 00:57:42,242
You're old enough to speak up, Kim Yumi!

892
00:57:52,450 --> 00:57:54,825
Let me sit beside you for a moment.

893
00:57:58,393 --> 00:58:00,742
We need to talk.

894
00:58:00,742 --> 00:58:03,440
- Pardon?
- You don't like working with me?

895
00:58:03,440 --> 00:58:05,116
What is it exactly?

896
00:58:10,614 --> 00:58:12,824
Could you be specific?

897
00:58:12,824 --> 00:58:15,209
I want an answer.

898
00:58:55,302 --> 00:58:57,867
<i>Wait, lightning? Out of a clear blue sky?</i>

899
00:58:57,867 --> 00:59:00,117
<i>- Hey! What the...
- Didn't he miss it intentionally?</i>

900
00:59:00,117 --> 00:59:02,700
<i>Come on, why?</i>

901
00:59:02,700 --> 00:59:04,209
<i>We're in trouble.</i>

902
00:59:04,209 --> 00:59:08,088
<i>The whole village is in chaos!</i>

903
00:59:08,088 --> 00:59:09,923
<i>Did Love Cell wake up?</i>

904
00:59:09,923 --> 00:59:11,341
<i>What for?</i>

905
00:59:11,341 --> 00:59:13,457
<i>- Thump, thump.
- Writer Kim.</i>

906
00:59:13,457 --> 00:59:15,720
<i>- Thump, thump.
- Thump, thump.</i>

907
00:59:15,720 --> 00:59:18,533
<i>Thump, thump.</i>

908
00:59:18,533 --> 00:59:21,754
<i>Why's her heart pounding out of nowhere?</i>

